# ─── Database ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by Prisma. On Vercel, this is fine for the dev environment.
# For production, swap to a real DB (PostgreSQL via Neon, Supabase, etc.)
# if you start persisting real data. For a portfolio with no DB features
# wired up yet, SQLite is fine.
DATABASE_URL=file:./dev.db

# ─── Admin token (bot-trap admin panel) ─────────────────────────────────
# Generate a strong random token: openssl rand -hex 32
# The admin panel is at yoursites.com/?admin=1
# DO NOT commit the real value to git — set this in Vercel env vars instead.
ADMIN_TOKEN=replace-with-openssl-rand-hex-32

# ─── Optional: Calendly (for the contact CTA) ──────────────────────────
# Currently hardcoded in hero.tsx and contact.tsx as
# https://calendly.com/baraarsreesha/intro — set this when you actually
# create the Calendly account.
# CALENDLY_URL=https://calendly.com/baraarsreesha/intro

# ─── Optional: analytics (free) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Vercel Analytics is built-in (no env var needed, just enable in dashboard)
# For Plausible: set up at plausible.io, then add the script domain here
# PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=baraarsreesha.com

# ─── Optional: Vercel KV for cross-instance bot-trap persistence ───────
# The free in-memory + /tmp bot-trap works per warm serverless instance.
# For full cross-instance persistence, sign up for Vercel KV (free tier:
# 256MB, 30k commands/mo) and uncomment these:
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# ─── Optional: external log sink for honeypot hits ─────────────────────
# Axiom (free 1GB/day) or Logtail (free 1GB/mo) — pipe console.warn
# honeypot logs there for permanent storage + searchability.
# AXIOM_TOKEN=
